@node lha "LHA Compression"
@version 0.121
@toc compression

    - LHA Compression -


        Usage: LhA [-<options>] <command> <archive[.LZH/LHA/RUN]>
                   [[homedir] <filespec>...] [@file] [destdir]


            Commands:

                a    add files to the archive
                c    concatenate archives
                d    delete files from archive
                e    extract files
                f    freshen files
                h    hunt for differences, archive <-> filesystem
                l[q] list archive, terse
                m    move files to archive
                p    print files to stdout
                r    replace files in archive
                t    test archive integrity
                u    update archive
                v[q] list archive, verbose
                vv   show archive contents, full
                x    extract files with full path



@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node compression.tutorial "Compression Tutorial"
@version 0.121
@toc compression

   2. Compression Tutorial


            Most compressors use a fairly standard method for extracting
        and compressing files. Here are some general rules, although they
        are not gauranteed to work with all compression programs.

            Assume that there is a file in RAM: called FAQ.lha.


       Listing

            Command: lha l FAQ.lha

                The following is a chart created by LHA version 1.38,
            which is freely distributable. The chart shows every file
            enclosed in the archive. These files generally can only be
            accessed after they are removed from the compressed archive.
            They may be removed all at once or one at a time. If a file
            is archived in a directory, the path name may also be
            extracted if you decide to do so.

    Listing of archive 'FAQ.lha':
    Original  Packed Ratio    Date     Time    Name
    -------- ------- ----- --------- --------  -------------
         610     215 64.7% 02-May-93 09:29:28  faq.hardware
         653     262 59.8% 02-May-93 09:28:28  faq.hardware.comparisons
        9830    2463 74.9% 02-May-93 11:32:52  faq.hardware.custom_chips
        3331     799 76.0% 02-May-93 08:14:54  faq.hardware.expansion
       33549    3232 90.3% 02-May-93 14:35:36  faq.hardware.models
        1481     478 67.7% 02-May-93 05:32:02  faq.hardware.monitors
        3087     939 69.5% 02-May-93 09:00:20  faq.hardware.processors
       18891    4176 77.8% 02-May-93 14:40:52  faq.hardware.screenmodes
        2564     678 73.5% 02-May-93 08:15:30  faq.hardware.storage
    -------- ------- ----- --------- --------
       73996   13242 82.1% 07-May-93 00:05:36   9 files

    Operation successful.


       Extracting

            Command: lha x FAQ.lha

                This will decompress a file and place the contents of
            the archive on disk. The archive will remain on disk also.

            Extracting from archive 'FAQ.lha':
            Extracting: (     610)  faq.hardware
            Extracting: (     653)  faq.hardware.comparisons
            Extracting: (    9830)  faq.hardware.custom_chips
            Extracting: (    3331)  faq.hardware.expansion
            Extracting: (   33549)  faq.hardware.models
            Extracting: (    1481)  faq.hardware.monitors
            Extracting: (    3087)  faq.hardware.processors
            Extracting: (   18891)  faq.hardware.screenmodes
            Extracting: (    2564)  faq.hardware.storage
            9 files extracted, all files OK.


            Operation successful.



