@node graphics.external "External Graphics Boards 0.180"
@toc hard.graphics

   6. External Graphics Boards

        These graphics boards should be compatible with all Amigas.


        - DCTV

            - NTSC or PAL
            - RGB optional
            - image capture in 10 seconds
                - color video cameras
                - still video cameras
                - video disk
                - still frame capable VCR's
            - paint and animation software included
            - compatible with other software packages
            - 1 megabyte RAM required
                - 3 or 5 megabytes RAM recommended

        - HAM-E

            - NTSC or PAL
            - RGB standard

        - Colorburst

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node opalvision "Opal Vision 0.180"
@toc hard.graphics

   p. Opal Vision


        - 24 BIT RGB output
        - video bandwidth greater than 7 MHz
        - 1.5 megabytes RAM
        - video slot capable
        - 24 BIT frame buffer
        - 16.8 million color palette
        - double buffered animation
            - 24 BIT or 15 BIT in low and medium resolutions
            - 8 BIT in all resolutions
        - VLSI graphics coprocessor
            - resolution changes
            - stencil modes
            - transition effects
            - smooth scrolling
        - screen colors update in realtime
        - dual playfield and overlay priority stencil modes
        - 20ns video switch
        - autoconfigures for NTSC and PAL
        - software included
            - Opal Paint
            - Opal Animate
        - video special effects chip (optional)
        - frame grabber and genlock module (optional)
        - scan rate converter (optional)
        - Roaster Chip for digital video effects (optional)

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node vivid24 "Vivid 24 0.180"
@toc hard.graphics

   x. Vivid 24


        - 24 BIT RGB output
        - 8 BIT Alpha channel
        - 160 MFLOPS
        - 100,000 shaded polygons per second
        - 2048x2048 interlaced resolution
        - 1280x1024 noninterlaced resolution
        - 40 MHz TMS34020 graphics processor
        - 4 graphics math coprocessors
        - broadcast quality video encoder
        - user programmable resolutions
        - 24 megabytes RAM
            - 16 megabytes Video RAM
            - 8 megabytes programmable RAM
        - video slot capable

        - 24 BIT frame buffer
        - 16.8 million color palette
        - software included
            - DMI Tweek
            - DMI Workbench
            - DMI Paint
            - DMI Render
            - SAGE
            - TMS340 Graphics Library

        Optional:

        - TMS34082 coprocessor with 128k 32 BIT static RAM module [2]
        - double TMS34082 graphics coprocessor with 256k 32 BIT static RAM [1]
        - video memory upgrade [4]
        - broadcast quality digital video encoder (NTSC, PAL, SVHS)
        - video effects generator requires video encoder module
        - 4 megabyte DRAM programmable memory upgrade



